						               													<description>From the box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Stimulating and absorbing, SAGA is an exciting chase through our Island's wonderful story and its fascinating legends&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The &amp;quot;islands&amp;quot; in this case being the British Isles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game comprises:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A board consisting of an outer circle and an inner spiral.&amp;#10;6 Playing Pieces&amp;#10;Pack of 36 SAGA cards (6 sets of 6 cards - each showing the date and details of a significant event in British history)&amp;#10;Pack of 16 BLACK SPOT cards (also showing other events in British history)&amp;#10;Dice&amp;#10;SAGA Bonds (money)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Traveling around the outside circle of the board each player has to try and collect five SAGA cards, each of a different color.  As each card is collected the player claims its cash value from the Exchequer (Bank).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the cash and five cards have been amassed, the player then moves to the center spiral and races towards the finish.  Each time a player lands on a Black Spot he must pay the penalty as shown on a BLACK SPOT card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the first player to reach the finish without going bankrupt.  Bankrupt players still have a chance to win - by going back to the start and beginning the journey through history again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
